modules.description: This module implements the Kuznechik block cipher algorithm, operating on 128-bit blocks using a key schedule derived from a provided key array. It supports encryption and decryption of individual data blocks using the cipher instance initialized with a specific key. Typical use cases include secure data encryption and decryption in cryptographic protocols or storage systems requiring the Kuznechik cipher.

This module implements the Kuznechik block cipher algorithm, providing encryption and decryption operations for 128-bit data blocks using a key-derived schedule. It works with byte arrays representing keys and data blocks, enabling secure cryptographic transformations. It is used in systems requiring Kuznechik-based encryption, such as secure storage or communication protocols.
